  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinate M&E works with architectural, structural and civil trades.</li><li>Manage and control M&E subcontractors, vendors and specialists.</li><li>Ensure works comply with approved drawings, method statements and specifications.</li><li>Monitor daily site progress, quality and safety.</li><li>Identify and resolve site coordination and technical issues.</li><li>Conduct site inspections, testing and inspections with consultants and authorities.</li><li>Review shop drawings, material submissions and method statements.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore codes and statutory requirements (BCA, SCDF, PUB, NEA, SP Group).</li><li>Coordinate and oversee testing, commissioning and authority approvals.</li><li>Prepare site records, inspection checklists and progress reports.</li><li>Manage rectification works, defects and final handover.</li><li>Support preparation of as-built drawings and O&M manuals.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or Building Services recognized by the PE Board.</li><li>Minimum 5 years M&E experience in large building or infrastructure projects.</li><li>Proven experience in large-scale project (arena, stadium, convention centre, airport, hospital preferred).</li><li>Strong knowledge of ACMV / HVAC systems, Electrical & ELV systems, Fire protection systems, Plumbing & drainage and BMS integration.</li><li>Able to read and coordinate M&E shop drawings and BIM models.</li><li>Strong site coordination and problem-solving skills.</li></ul>",
